don't you know!

67
00:04:31,698 --> 00:04:33,532
Now, should I turn this
into the police,

68
00:04:33,665 --> 00:04:36,432
or give it
to its rightful owner?

69
00:04:36,565 --> 00:04:39,165
You-- You wouldn't dare!
Oh, lookie!

70
00:04:39,298 --> 00:04:41,198
The owner happens
to be right there.

71
00:04:41,332 --> 00:04:44,032
Doing the honorable thing
just got even more convenient!

72
00:04:44,165 --> 00:04:46,632
No, you idiot!
You know what'll happen
if you give it back?

73
00:04:46,765 --> 00:04:48,332
[grunts]
Think about your boy!

74
00:04:48,465 --> 00:04:51,232
He and the Dullahan's body
were in love, weren't they?

75
00:04:51,365 --> 00:04:53,165
If it gets the head back,

76
00:04:53,298 --> 00:04:54,632
Kujiragi said it'd forget

77
00:04:54,765 --> 00:04:57,432
all its memories
of its life in Ikebukuro!

78
00:04:57,565 --> 00:04:59,498
[scoffs]
Don't even worry about it!

79
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:01,532
Believe me,
my son can take it.

80
00:05:01,665 --> 00:05:03,598
Even if Celty did
forget all about him,

81
00:05:03,732 --> 00:05:05,598
I'm sure he'll find
a way to win her back,

82
00:05:05,732 --> 00:05:07,632
even if it takes him
another 20 years!

83
00:05:07,765 --> 00:05:09,132
[chuckles, grunts]

84
00:05:10,865 --> 00:05:13,132
Uh, well... [chuckles]
Like the doctor said,

85
00:05:13,265 --> 00:05:15,698
you can't break an omelet
without making a few eggs!

86
