[laughing]
I think you're using
the wrong proverb, doctor.

87
00:05:20,065 --> 00:05:23,132
And you don't break omelets,
you make them.

88
00:05:23,265 --> 00:05:25,532
Yeah, well...
let's talk about it later.

89
00:05:25,665 --> 00:05:27,632
Resume the experiment, Egor!

90
00:05:29,865 --> 00:05:31,232
You can't do this!

91
00:05:33,665 --> 00:05:36,165
No, don't!

92
00:05:41,398 --> 00:05:43,065
[neighs]

93
00:05:43,198 --> 00:05:44,165
Mm.

94
00:05:44,298 --> 00:05:45,432
[grunts]

95
00:05:45,565 --> 00:05:48,465
I knew it.
Shizuo was bad luck.

96
00:05:49,485 --> 00:05:51,485
Tonight's transaction
was a failure.

97
00:05:51,485 --> 00:05:55,718
I was so distracted,
I let my guard down
on the Dullahan.

98
00:06:22,711 --> 00:06:26,985
Hi, Celty. How does it feel
to have your head back again?

99
00:06:26,985 --> 00:06:28,451
And who might you be?

100
00:06:28,451 --> 00:06:30,218
What a shame.

101
00:06:30,218 --> 00:06:34,151
It looks like
the Celty I used to know
is gone for good.

102
00:06:34,151 --> 00:06:36,085
Well, I'd love for us
to get re-acquainted,

103
00:06:36,218 --> 00:06:38,285
but, right now,
I have other plans.

104
00:06:38,418 --> 00:06:42,051
You seem to be busy yourself.
So, see you around!

105
00:06:42,185 --> 00:06:45,018
You should forget
you ever saw me, human.

106
00:06:45,151 --> 00:06:46,651
Hmph.

107
00:06:46,785 --> 00:06:48,785
As if that's even possible.

108
00:06:48,918 --> 00:06:50,818
I don't care about you.

109
00:06:50,951 --> 00:06:54,631
After all, I love humans!

110
00:06:57,451 --> 00:06:59,871
Damn it! What the hell's
Kyohei thinkin',

111
00:06:59,871 --> 00:07:01,605
runnin' around
out there alone?

112
00:07:01,605 --> 00:07:04,571
Come on, let's move, man!
What if this is his Death Flag?

113
00:07:04,571 --> 00:07:07,105
We have to get to him
before the corpse looters do!

114
00:07:07,105 --> 00:07:09,638
[doorbell rings]
[both gasp]

115
00:07:12,071 --> 00:07:13,671
[stammering]

116
00:07:13,805 --> 00:07:15,805
Kyohei!

117
00:07:15,938 --> 00:07:17,171
'Sup.

118
00:07:18,305 --> 00:07:19,738
Anyway, I thought
if I came here,

119
00:07:19,871 --> 00:07:22,271
I'd find whatever
painkillers or meds I needed.

120
00:07:22,405 --> 00:07:25,138
Well, I, for one, think
you made a very wise choice!

121
00:07:25,271 --> 00:07:27,938
Yeah, you can say that again.

122
00:07:28,071 --> 00:07:30,405
You should've just stayed
in the hospital, but no!

123
00:07:30,538 --> 00:07:34,438
You gotta be out, alone,
lookin' for the dick
that ran you down, don't ya?

124
00:07:34,571 --> 00:07:37,638
What if you died?
What's gonna happen
to me and Erika?

125
00:07:37,771 --> 00:07:39,871
Scratch that, what about
her hot friend Azusa?

126
00:07:40,005 --> 00:07:43,138
You know she's into you,
so why you gotta
be all suicidal?

127
00:07:43,271 --> 00:07:45,105
She's 3D, man!

128
00:07:45,238 --> 00:07:47,371
You can't ignore
a flag like that
when it pops up!

129
00:07:47,505 --> 00:07:50,805
Do what you want,
but let us help once
in a while, goddamn it!

130
00:07:50,938 --> 00:07:53,671
Yeah, well, things aren't
as simple as that.

131
00:07:53,805 --> 00:07:55,338
Hey, where's Erika?

132
00:07:55,471 --> 00:07:58,271
Where do you think she is?
Out there, lookin' for you.

133
00:07:58,405 --> 00:08:01,071
You gotta call her now
and tell her to get
her ass over here.

134
00:08:01,205 --> 00:08:04,271
And, if she can't, tell her
to get back to her pad
and lock the door.

135
00:08:04,405 --> 00:08:06,738
Why are you stressin'?
She can handle herself.
You know that.

136
00:08:06,871 --> 00:08:09,838
I didn't come here
for a couple of aspirin
and a visit.

137
00:08:09,971 --> 00:08:13,371
I need to talk to Celty
about something I saw
when I got hit.

138
00:08:13,505 --> 00:08:16,638
Those people that hit me,
somethin' was up with 'em.

139
00:08:16,771 --> 00:08:18,505
Celty might know what.

140
00:08:18,638 --> 00:08:21,671
On the way over in the cab,
I saw tons of 'em out there.

141
00:08:21,805 --> 00:08:24,738
Tons of what out there?
People, I guess.

142
00:08:24,871 --> 00:08:28,238
<i>I don't know,</i>
<i>but it's a mess out there.</i>

143
00:08:29,738 --> 00:08:33,738
Damn it. Shizuo's got an excuse,
but Varona ditchin' work?

144
00:08:33,871 --> 00:08:38,171
I tell ya, Dennis,
makin' the rounds today
straight up sucked.

145
00:08:38,305 --> 00:08:40,238
And, now, thanks to
that bombing, or whatever,

146
00:08:40,371 --> 00:08:41,971
