<i>that happened with him</i>
<i>and the Dollars.</i>

206
00:11:22,471 --> 00:11:28,271
<i>Something supernatural,</i>
<i>something extraordinary,</i>
<i>but, still...</i>

207
00:11:28,405 --> 00:11:30,738
[thinking] <i>I feel like</i>
<i>I couldn't care less.</i>

208
00:11:30,871 --> 00:11:32,571
<i>What's wrong with me?</i>

209
00:11:32,705 --> 00:11:36,138
<i>It's like</i>
<i>I'm not myself anymore.</i>

210
00:11:36,271 --> 00:11:38,405
<i>That day,</i>
<i>I found myself</i>

211
00:11:38,538 --> 00:11:40,738
<i>standing someplace</i>
<i>I'd never seen before.</i>

212
00:11:40,871 --> 00:11:44,071
[Tom]
<i>He might end up</i>
<i>killing someone.</i>

213
00:11:44,205 --> 00:11:46,438
<i>Or, he might end up</i>
<i>getting killed.</i>

214
00:11:46,571 --> 00:11:48,538
<i>Or, even killing himself.</i>

215
00:11:48,671 --> 00:11:50,405
[thinking]
<i>But I don't want to die,</i>

216
00:11:50,538 --> 00:11:53,238
<i>and I don't want</i>
<i>to kill anyone.</i>

217
00:11:53,371 --> 00:11:55,071
Well, it's mine now,

218
00:11:55,205 --> 00:11:56,938
so the least I can do
is try it out.

219
00:11:57,071 --> 00:11:58,605
I think the deal is,

220
00:11:58,738 --> 00:12:00,905
I'm supposed to keep
my finger off the trigger,

221
00:12:01,038 --> 00:12:02,438
until I fire it.

222
00:12:16,505 --> 00:12:17,665
[laughing]

223
00:12:26,465 --> 00:12:30,406
Izaya! I saw you guys
fighting yesterday.
That was awesome!

224
00:12:30,406 --> 00:12:32,740
Seriously?
That wasn't awesome.

225
00:12:32,873 --> 00:12:37,073
I was almost killed
by a single-celled monster,
posing as a human.

226
00:12:37,206 --> 00:12:38,806
<i>What's up</i>
<i>with that guy, anyway?</i>

227
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:40,873
<i>I lured him right</i>
<i>in front of that truck,</i>

228
00:12:41,006 --> 00:12:44,473
<i>and he got up after</i>
<i>like it was no big deal.</i>

229
00:12:44,606 --> 00:12:46,606
'Cause he's awesome!
I can't believe

230
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:48,940
you're not excited about
meeting a guy like him.

231
00:12:49,073 --> 00:12:52,140
You did say you were
interested in humans,
didn't you?

232
00:12:52,273 --> 00:12:53,773
He is not human.

233
00:12:53,906 --> 00:12:56,606
He's either some kind
of wild animal, or a monster.

234
00:12:56,740 --> 00:12:58,540
I was kinda hopin'
you guys would get along,

235
00:12:58,673 --> 00:13:00,606
'cause it'd be better that way.

236
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:02,640
If you didn't get along,
you guys could end up

237
00:13:02,773 --> 00:13:04,873
enemies, or arch-rivals,
or something.

238
00:13:05,006 --> 00:13:08,173
If that happened,
someone could get hurt
before you know it.

239
00:13:08,306 --> 00:13:11,473
Or maybe even worse.
Maybe one of you guys
might end up dying.

240
00:13:11,606 --> 00:13:13,240
If it worries you so much,

241
00:13:13,373 --> 00:13:15,806
why in God's name
did you introduce us?

242
00:13:15,940 --> 00:13:19,073
I always thought
if worse came to worse,
I could smooth things over.

243
00:13:19,206 --> 00:13:22,506
Oh, well! It didn't work out,
but it was a good try.

244
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:24,373
If you guys end up
killing each other,

245
00:13:24,506 --> 00:13:26,573
I'll have two new openings
on my friends list.

246
00:13:26,706 --> 00:13:29,273
If that's how it is,
so be it.

247
00:13:29,406 --> 00:13:31,373
Some friend
you turned out to be.

248
00:13:31,506 --> 00:13:33,273
Sorry, that's how it is!

249
00:13:33,406 --> 00:13:35,840
In the end, I don't care
if everyone in the world dies.

250
00:13:35,973 --> 00:13:39,406
The only thing
that matters to me is that
the woman I love survives!

251
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:41,540
By the way,
have you heard the saying,

252
00:13:41,673 --> 00:13:43,306
"A tiger dies
and leaves its skin,

253
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,073
but people die
and leave their names"?

254
00:13:45,206 --> 00:13:48,173
No.
Shizuo's kinda like a tiger.

255
00:13:48,306 --> 00:13:52,206
When he dies,
he'll leave behind stories
of how strong he was.

256
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:55,473
People will treasure
those heroic tales
and tell them over and over,

257
00:13:55,606 --> 00:13:57,673
and, eventually,
he'll become an urban legend!

258
00:13:57,806 --> 00:14:00,373
Yes! I said "legend,"
not "rumor"!

259
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,473
There's a huge difference,
don't you know!

260
00:14:02,606 --> 00:14:05,940
There's even a chance
he could surpass
his urban-legendary status

261
00:14:06,073 --> 00:14:09,473
and live on in people's hearts
as a superhuman entity!

262
00:14:09,606 --> 00:14:12,340
[thinking]
<i>That barbarian, a legend?</i>

263
00:14:12,473 --> 00:14:14,440
<i>A superhuman entity?</i>

264
00:14:14,573 --> 00:14:17,673
<i>That's insane.</i>
<i>That guy's a monster, at best.</i>

265
00:14:17,806 --> 00:14:21,706
Okay. If tigers leaving skins
behind is true, what about you?

266
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:24,873
What kind of achievement
will you leave?
If I were to guess,

267
00:14:25,006 --> 00:14:27,973
you'd leave behind a legacy
as a serial killer,

268
00:14:28,106 --> 00:14:30,006
and that thrills me!

269
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:33,173
Well, I'm human, so I'd...

270
00:14:36,340 --> 00:14:38,140
<i>...I don't care.</i>

271
00:14:41,106 --> 00:14:42,573
[liquid sloshes]

272
00:14:59,273 --> 00:15:01,640
[chuckles]
Guess it's started!

273
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:08,540
Izaya!

274
00:15:08,673 --> 00:15:10,173
[chuckles]

275
00:15:10,306 --> 00:15:11,840
[Tom]
<i>And, once again,</i>

276
00:15:11,973 --> 00:15:15,206
<i>I got caught up in shit</i>
<i>that's beyond trippy.</i>

277
00:15:15,340 --> 00:15:16,673
We're so screwed.

278
00:15:16,806 --> 00:15:18,906
Please tell me
this is a nightmare.

279
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:21,440
[sarcastically] Oh, great.
They're all Saika zombies.

280
00:15:21,573 --> 00:15:23,640
Hey, wait.
You know what's with 'em?

281
00:15:23,773 --> 00:15:25,140
I'm Kine.

282
00:15:25,273 --> 00:15:27,240
[thinking]
<i>Kine? Isn't he ex-Awakusu?</i>

283
00:15:27,373 --> 00:15:31,240
I'm Tanaka.
What's goin' on out there
is sort of complicated,

284
00:15:31,373 --> 00:15:32,840
so I'll give you
the short version.

285
00:15:32,973 --> 00:15:34,373
It's a kind of a hypnosis

286
00:15:34,506 --> 00:15:36,240
that forces people
to do what you want.

287
00:15:36,373 --> 00:15:38,740
You're shittin' me!
Then, that means

288
00:15:38,873 --> 00:15:41,106
there's gotta
be someone out there,
who did the hypnotizin'!

289
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,773
You catch on quick, pal.

290
00:15:42,906 --> 00:15:45,173
I know a couple of people
who can do stuff like this,

291
00:15:45,306 --> 00:15:47,340
but I can't think
of a reason why any of them

292
00:15:47,473 --> 00:15:49,073
would wanna surround
a sushi joint.

293
00:15:49,206 --> 00:15:50,906
How 'bout you, boss man?

294
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:53,740
You got any reason
why someone would wanna
give you trouble?

295
00:15:53,873 --> 00:15:56,040
No idea. Maybe they're
after you guys.

296
00:15:56,173 --> 00:16:00,040
No, I'm pretty sure
I haven't pissed off
any hypnotists lately.

297
00:16:00,173 --> 00:16:02,040
Maybe you didn't, smart-ass,

298
00:16:02,173 --> 00:16:03,906
but maybe someone
you're tight with did.

299
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:06,340
You ever think of that?
Oh.

300
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:15,273
[sighs] Man, I think
I might know some folks
like that, after all,

301
00:16:15,406 --> 00:16:18,606
Hey! We have fun
sleepover tonight, <i>da</i> ?

302
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:20,706
Have plenty firecracker
to go around!

303
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:25,306
Hey! You know how I feel
about arming the customers!

304
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:28,106
Damn! That's some arsenal!

305
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:32,306
Totally illegal to have
in this country, but... damn.

306
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:35,506
This is a flash grenade.
It's army shit.

307
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:38,406
Fire and fight
are purple of Edo.

308
00:16:38,540 --> 00:16:41,806
But is no good, fight.
Face get purple.

309
00:16:41,940 --> 00:16:44,540
Instead of campfire,
we shoot firework,

310
00:16:44,673 --> 00:16:47,006
then Tamai-ya
and Kagiya friendly!

311
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:51,806
[Tom]
<i>Man, shit just crossed over</i>
<i>from trippy to off-the-hook.</i>

312
00:16:51,940 --> 00:16:54,906
[overlapping voices]
<i>I love you.</i>

313
00:16:56,073 --> 00:16:58,106
What's wrong, Anri? You okay?

314
00:16:58,240 --> 00:16:59,740
Yes, I'm fine.

315
00:16:59,873 --> 00:17:03,006
I don't know, you don't look it.
Wanna stop and rest?

316
00:17:03,140 --> 00:17:05,506
I'll be okay.

317
00:17:11,540 --> 00:17:13,706
[gasps]
And speakin' of Anri...

318
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:15,873
yeah, I saw her
with a sword like that.

319
00:17:16,006 --> 00:17:18,573
I don't know
what's goin' on anymore!
This is all news to me!

320
00:17:18,706 --> 00:17:20,406
I can't even get
my head around it!

321
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:22,606
Guess this means
you don't know your friends

322
00:17:22,740 --> 00:17:25,840
as good as you thought
you did, huh, son?

323
00:17:25,973 --> 00:17:29,173
Mikado! You up there?

324
00:17:29,306 --> 00:17:30,706
Is something wrong?

325
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:32,440
You know that psycho
that was going off at you

326
00:17:32,573 --> 00:17:34,406
in the chatroom
a little while ago?

327
00:17:34,540 --> 00:17:36,340
Well, now,
some other psycho logged on,

328
00:17:36,473 --> 00:17:39,206
and they're saying all kinds
of stuff about Masaomi Kida.

329
00:17:41,673 --> 00:17:43,806
<i>Sorry to interrupt</i>
<i>your conversation!</i>

330
00:17:43,940 --> 00:17:47,273
<i>I hope you haven't logged</i>
<i>off yet. That would suck.</i>

331
00:17:47,406 --> 00:17:49,773
<i>It's been a while since</i>
<i>I was on one of these things.</i>

332
00:17:49,906 --> 00:17:52,106
<i>These days, I kick it</i>
<i>on social networks.</i>

333
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:55,106
[Namie]
<i>Who are you? This isn't</i>
<i>your business, so leave.</i>

334
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:59,173
<i>Hey, you're a girl, right?</i>
<i>I can tell by the handle.</i>
<i>It's cute!</i>

335
00:17:59,306 --> 00:18:00,973
<i>I'd love to meet up</i>
<i>with you in real life,</i>

336
00:18:01,106 --> 00:18:03,306
<i>but, right now,</i>
<i>I gotta hijack this chat,</i>

337
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:06,506
<i>'cause I got something to say.</i>
<i>Sorry 'bout that.</i>

338
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:09,273
<i>See, I got a stake</i>
<i>in this, too.</i>

339
00:18:09,406 --> 00:18:11,406
<i>'Sup, Mikado Ryugamine.</i>

340
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:18,106
<i>Let me guess,</i>
<i>you didn't pick up</i>

341
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:20,306
<i>'cause it was from a number</i>
<i>you didn't know.</i>

342
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:24,640
<i>It was me. Truth is,</i>
<i>we met a while ago.</i>

343
00:18:24,773 --> 00:18:27,740
<i>Anyway, if someone's</i>
<i>callin' you, pick up.</i>

344
00:18:27,873 --> 00:18:30,106
<i>If you're reading this,</i>
<i>hit the redial.</i>

345
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:32,306
<i>If you don't,</i>
<i>Masaomi Kida's gonna be</i>

346
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:35,140
<i>in some deep shit, for real.</i>

347
00:18:35,273 --> 00:18:38,306
<i>You don't wanna let your boy</i>
<i>suffer any more, do ya?</i>

348
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:40,673
<i>Shut up! Who cares</i>
<i>about any of that?</i>

349
00:18:40,806 --> 00:18:43,706
<i>Go away! Mikado,</i>
<i>do what I told you!</i>

350
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:47,373
<i>By the way,</i>
<i>how's Seiji doing?</i>
<i>What?</i>

351
00:18:47,506 --> 00:18:49,306
<i>I hope he's good.</i>
<i>I wonder what he'd think,</i>

352
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:51,706
<i>if he saw how aggro</i>
<i>you were being here.</i>

353
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:54,140
<i>Don't screw with me, you--</i>
[grumbles incoherently]

354
00:18:54,273 --> 00:18:57,440
[Kururi]
<i>Wow. This chat took a turn</i>
<i>for the bizarre, didn't it?</i>

355
00:18:57,573 --> 00:18:58,840
[Mairu]
<i>How intense!</i>

356
00:18:58,973 --> 00:19:00,740
[ringtone meowing]
Ooh!

357
00:19:00,873 --> 00:19:03,706
Hey! What do you know,
your boy's callin'.

358
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:06,306
Easy, bruh! I gotta
be the one to answer,

359
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:07,773
or the trick ain't gonna work!

360
00:19:07,906 --> 00:19:09,840
No, I think I should
be the one to.

361
00:19:09,973 --> 00:19:11,406
But when he hears your voice,

362
00:19:11,540 --> 00:19:13,373
he'll know you're okay
and he'll hang up.

363
00:19:13,506 --> 00:19:16,640
Uh, before I answer this,
I'm sorry.

364
00:19:16,773 --> 00:19:17,640
Huh?

365
00:19:17,773 --> 00:19:19,240
'Sup!

366
00:19:20,173 --> 00:19:22,073
Are you Rocchi
from the chatroom?

367
00:19:22,206 --> 00:19:26,106
<i>Yup! Glad you got my message.</i>
<i>Thanks for callin' back.</i>

368
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,306
<i>So, recognize my voice?</i>

369
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:30,840
I do. You're
Chikage Rokujo, right?

370
00:19:30,973 --> 00:19:33,073
Right on! Good memory!

371
00:19:33,206 --> 00:19:35,406
You deserve a standing
ovation for that.

372
00:19:35,540 --> 00:19:37,673
I don't know
if you remember
the day we met.

373
00:19:37,806 --> 00:19:41,573
I should've believed you
when you said you were
the boss of the Dollars.

374
00:19:41,706 --> 00:19:43,340
<i>It's nice</i>
<i>catchin' up and all,</i>

375
00:19:43,473 --> 00:19:45,040
<i>but let me cut</i>
<i>to the chase here.</i>

376
00:19:45,173 --> 00:19:47,273
Those Dollar-bros
of yours thought

377
00:19:47,406 --> 00:19:49,606
it was a good idea
to mess with my crew again.

378
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:51,873
So, I came back
to make you pay for it.

379
00:19:52,006 --> 00:19:53,240
Uh--
[screaming]

380
00:19:53,373 --> 00:19:56,173
[screaming continues]

381
00:19:56,306 --> 00:19:59,373
You heard that, yeah?
I wanna see you, one-on-one.

382
00:19:59,506 --> 00:20:02,440
Blow me off and you'll never
see your pal again, got it?

383
00:20:02,573 --> 00:20:04,040
[gasps]

384
00:20:04,173 --> 00:20:07,840
Piece of cake!
Now, I know where to go.

385
00:20:07,973 --> 00:20:09,840
Come on, hostage!
We're goin' downtown

386
00:20:09,973 --> 00:20:11,706
to drop you off
with your boy.

387
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,706
See? Told you I'd figure out
how to get you guys together!

388
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:17,473
Yeah, but I never said
I was gonna be your hostage!

389
00:20:17,606 --> 00:20:19,940
Damn it. Why'd you have
to kick me like that for?

390
00:20:20,073 --> 00:20:21,906
[chuckling]
Oh, come on, man!

391
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,540
I apologized first,
didn't I?

392
00:20:23,673 --> 00:20:25,540
I could've acted
like you were hurting me,

393
00:20:25,673 --> 00:20:28,140
instead of you kicking me
in the goddamn knee!

394
00:20:28,273 --> 00:20:29,640
Where are we
meeting up with him?

395
00:20:29,773 --> 00:20:31,740
I couldn't hear his side
of the conversation.

396
00:20:31,873 --> 00:20:34,973
It's a part of town I know
pretty well, actually.

397
00:20:35,106 --> 00:20:36,640
It's like a second home.

398
00:20:37,013 --> 00:20:39,654
There's a school for chicks
around the corner.

399
00:20:39,654 --> 00:20:42,620
Now what? You're not really
gonna go there alone.

400
00:20:42,754 --> 00:20:44,120
Huh? Oh.

401
00:20:44,254 --> 00:20:46,154
Well, he said one-on-one,

402
00:20:46,287 --> 00:20:47,454
so I don't really
have a choice.

403
00:20:47,587 --> 00:20:49,120
Rokujo's dangerous.

404
00:20:49,254 --> 00:20:51,854
We messed with the Toramaru
once and he's their boss.

405
00:20:51,987 --> 00:20:53,387
Instead of you
going to meet him,

406
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:55,020
what if me and the guys
hop in the car

407
00:20:55,154 --> 00:20:56,754
and bring Masaomi back here?

408
00:20:56,887 --> 00:20:58,354
Why would you take that risk?

409
00:20:58,487 --> 00:21:00,854
I mean, it's not like
Masaomi's a friend of yours.

410
00:21:00,987 --> 00:21:04,487
Oh, well, he's a friend
of yours, isn't he?

411
00:21:04,620 --> 00:21:07,087
Yeah, but he's also the leader
of the Yellow Scarves,

412
00:21:07,220 --> 00:21:08,687
so that makes him your enemy.

413
00:21:08,820 --> 00:21:10,254
Now, I see what
you're getting at.

414
00:21:10,387 --> 00:21:12,120
I can't speak for my brother,
but I can tell you

415
00:21:12,254 --> 00:21:14,220
me and my guys
never fought him.

416
00:21:14,354 --> 00:21:16,954
As far as I'm concerned,
we don't hold any grudges
against him.

417
00:21:17,087 --> 00:21:19,654
He's not a friend, or an enemy.
He's just another guy.

418
00:21:19,787 --> 00:21:23,154
So, if you want us to go over
there and get him, say the word.

419
00:21:23,287 --> 00:21:25,054
We'll bring him back
safe and sound.

420
00:21:25,187 --> 00:21:26,854
I'd appreciate it if you did.

421
00:21:26,987 --> 00:21:29,020
Still, if you show up,

422
00:21:29,154 --> 00:21:31,820
do you think Masaomi's
just gonna trust you?

423
00:21:31,954 --> 00:21:34,420
He jokes around a lot,
but he doesn't like
being played.

424
00:21:34,554 --> 00:21:36,820
Seeing you might
make him suspicious.

425
00:21:36,954 --> 00:21:40,520
By the way, how come
you decided on that place
to have the meeting?

426
00:21:40,654 --> 00:21:43,154
[sighs]

427
00:21:43,287 --> 00:21:45,120
It's important to me.

428
00:21:45,254 --> 00:21:47,254
I think I told you about it.

429
00:21:47,387 --> 00:21:51,687
It's where it all began,
for me and for the Dollars.

430
00:21:51,820 --> 00:21:56,220
But, that night, neither
Anri or Masaomi were there.

431
00:21:56,354 --> 00:21:58,820
[Tom]
<i>In case you haven't</i>
<i>figured it out yet,</i>

432
00:21:58,954 --> 00:22:03,254
<i>there ain't much difference</i>
<i>between what's ordinary</i>
<i>and extraordinary.</i>

433
00:22:03,387 --> 00:22:06,954
<i>Hell, if you ask me,</i>
<i>I'd say this was ordinary.</i>

434
00:22:07,087 --> 00:22:09,220
<i>But... am I cool with it?</i>

435
00:22:09,354 --> 00:22:11,820
<i>Yeah, I don't know about that.</i>

436
00:22:11,954 --> 00:22:13,654
<i>I mean, life is short, right?</i>

437
00:22:13,787 --> 00:22:16,120
<i>So, what's the point of livin'</i>
<i>unless you're havin' fun?</i>

438
00:22:16,254 --> 00:22:17,787
<i>That's where</i>
<i>I'm comin' from.</i>

439
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:20,154
<i>I just want</i>
<i>my old life back, man.</i>

440
00:22:20,287 --> 00:22:22,320
[whispering]
What's going on?

441
00:22:22,454 --> 00:22:23,854
<i>Please?</i>

442
00:22:23,987 --> 00:22:25,920
[overlapping voices]
<i>I love you.</i>

443
00:22:27,154 --> 00:22:30,620
♪ [theme song playing]

444
00:23:57,454 --> 00:24:00,320
[Akabayashi]
<i>What should I do?</i>
<i>What can I do?</i>

445
00:24:00,320 --> 00:24:02,320
<i>I don't even know</i>
<i>how to process</i>

446
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:04,487
<i>the shit that's goin' on</i>
<i>in this city.</i>

447
00:24:04,487 --> 00:24:06,920
<i>Next time:</i>
<i>Walking On Thin Ice.</i>

448
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:10,620
<i>You know what? I think</i>
